
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes and relationships

class ResearchGroup {
    +String name
    +Department department
    +List<Researcher> members
    +List<WorkPackage> ledWPs
}

class Department {
    +String name
    +List<ResearchGroup> groups
}

class Researcher {
    +String id
    +String name
    +ResearchGroup currentGroup
    +List<Assignment> assignments
}

class WorkPackage {
    +String id
    +String title
    +ResearchGroup leader
    +Project project
    +List<Assignment> teamMembers
}

class Assignment {
    +Date startDate
    +Date endDate (optional)
    +Role role
    +Researcher researcher
    +WorkPackage workPackage
}

class Project {
    +String id
    +String title
    +List<WorkPackage> workPackages
}

' Relationships

Department "1" *-- "many" ResearchGroup : has
ResearchGroup "1" *-- "many" Researcher : has
ResearchGroup "1" *-- "many" WorkPackage : leads

WorkPackage "1" *-- "many" Assignment : hasTeamMembers
WorkPackage "1" 1-- "1" ResearchGroup : isLedBy

Project "1" *-- "many" WorkPackage : has
Researcher "1" *-- "many" Assignment : assignedTo
Assignment "1" 1-- "1" Researcher : hasResearcher
Assignment "1" 1-- "1" WorkPackage : hasWP

enum Role {
    LEADER
    TEAM_MEMBER
}

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **ResearchGroup**: Represents a group of researchers. Each belongs to one department.
- **Department**: Contains multiple research groups.
- **Researcher**: Belongs to exactly one `ResearchGroup` at any time. Has many assignments to WPs.
- **WorkPackage (WP)**: A part of a project. Led by one `ResearchGroup`, can have team members from any group.
- **Assignment**: Tracks when a researcher was assigned to a WP, with start/end dates and role (e.g., LEADER or TEAM_MEMBER).
- **Project**: Composed of multiple WPs.
- **Role**: An enum to differentiate between roles in an assignment.

---

This diagram ensures **traceability** of service delivery between research groups via the `Assignment` class, and handles the requirement that assignments are terminated/created when a researcher changes groups or a WP's leadership changes.

